Make dashi: Wipe any sand or salt from kombu with a dampened cloth. Bring kombu and water just to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan over high heat. Remove kombu with tongs and reserve for another use.
Sprinkle katsuo bushi over liquid and remove pan from heat. Let stand 3 minutes, then pour through a cheesecloth-lined sieve into a bowl.
Prepare soup: Stir together misto and 1/4 cup dashi in a bowl until smooth. Heat remaining dashi in saucepan over moderately high heat until hot, then gently stir in tofu. Simmer 1minute and remove from heat. Immediately stir in miso mixture and and scallion greens and serve.
